{"title":"String spokes and feathery disc rotors: Chris Hall’s lightweight Cervélo R5","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/chris-hall-cervelo-r5-hill-climb-championship-2023","date":1698928613000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/chris-hall-cervelo-r5-hill-climb-championship-2023\">String spokes and feathery disc rotors: Chris Hall’s lightweight Cervélo R5</a></p>\n\n<p>Chris Hall is best known for his wild endurance challenges, such as riding 107km for 107 days in a row, but he got the bug for short and sharp efforts at last year’s National Hill Climb Championship. This year, he’s back and the focus simple: build a bike that is incredibly light but still real-world usable. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘Aside from the gearing, which may be a bit on the spinny side, it’s still a completely rideable bike outside of hill climbs,’ says Hall. ‘You know, a bike you could actually ride down the hill on as well as up it.’ </p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/cannondale-supersix-evo-hill-climb-bike\">Carbon brake calipers and a broken stem: The sub-4.6kg Cannondale SuperSix Evo</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-road-bike\">Best road bikes: Best bikes from under £1,000 to over £10,000</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/gifts-for-cyclists\">Best gifts for cyclists: Presents for the cyclist in your life</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<p>Unlike hill climb builds, there isn’t a sawn-off handlebar or electrical-taped lever in sight on Hall’s Paris-Roubaix edition Cervélo R5, but that doesn’t mean it has skimped on the lightweight tech. The saddle, bars and stem are all Schmolke carbon numbers, with a Darimo seatpost completing the finishing kit. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>pièce de résistance</em>, however, is the wheels. Hand-built – or should we say hand-strung – the week of the event, the Strada wheels see ExtraLite Cyber laced to Reserve carbon rims with Berd polymer string spokes for a true weight-weenie set up. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep scrolling for close ups of the full build. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-11-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>‘Over fast’ – the hill climber’s dream/mantra.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-970x647.jpg\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cervelo_chris_hall_hill_climb_national_2023-21-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Galfer Road Wave rotors shave weight off the brake setup. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"